OL,7,FNonetheless, even when correcting for
OL,8,Fthe seasonal distortion, the average
OL,9,Fgrowth for March and April together
OL,10,Fwas only 0.2%, down on the three-month
OL,11,Faverage of 0.5% and the 12-month
OL,12,Faverage of 2.2%.
OL,14,FAnalysts said that while consumers
OL,15,Fshould have started feeling more
OL,16,Fconfident to spend amid falling
OL,17,Finflation and the prospect of interest
OL,18,Frate cuts from the Bank of England,
OL,19,Fthat had not yet come to fruition.
