OL,7,FFood sales increased 4.4% year-on-
OL,8,Fyear, against a growth of 9.8% in
OL,9,FApril 2023, while non-food sales
OL,10,Fdecreased 2.8% for the same period.
OL,12,FTech sales saw a slight boost as
OL,13,Fpeople sought out upgrades for
OL,14,Fcomputers, phones and other devices a
OL,15,Ffew years after the pandemic-induced
OL,16,Fsurge in activity in the sector.
OL,18,FBut typical spring purposes such as
OL,19,Fclothing and shoes, DIY equipment and
OL,20,Fgarden furniture were weak, as a
OL,21,Fresult of the dull, wet weather.
